1/6. Drama set in France during the Second World War and based on true events. On Armistice Day, teenager Lili is caught by the police laying flowers at the foot of a hero's statue. This triggers a string of events that sees her thrown together with like-minded students opposing German occupation. Meanwhile, a small group of committed rebels secretly joins forces to produce a newspaper called Resistance. Lili and her friend `The Kid' undertake the dangerous job of distributing copies and begin to fall in love.
